      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/manorhaven/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Locals coined the name Manorhaven by blending 'Manor' and 'Haven' to capture the community’s welcoming spirit.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25,
        26,
        27
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manorhaven%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The village sits atop the Harbor Hill Moraine, a terminal moraine carved by glaciers during the Wisconsin Glacial Episode.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        30
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manorhaven%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1930 a ferry began running from Bowman's Point Road in Manorhaven to New Rochelle, operating until 1939 when the Bronx‑Whitestone Bridge opened.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11,
        12,
